whereas.text:
Whereas for months Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) has been engaged in an almost unchecked campaign of murder and mayhem across a broad swath of
			 Iraq and Syria that has killed thousands of innocent people and terrorized
			 millions;

Whereas the threat posed by the recruitment of ISIL fighters in the United States and Europe and
			 the prospect of these fighters returning to the United States or allied
			 countries jeopardizes the security of the United States and its allies;

Whereas ISIL poses an unusual and extraordinary threat to the national security and foreign policy
			 of the United States and if left unchecked will be the locus of plots to
			 attack our homeland;
